HEADWORD: Sapience
<hw>Sa"pi*ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sapientia</ets>: cf. F. <ets>sapience</ets>. See
<er>Sapient</er>..]</ety> <def>The quality of being sapient; wisdom;
sageness; knowledge.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Woman, if I might sit beside your feet,⟦br⟧
And glean your scattered <qex>sapience</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sapient</ent>⟦br⟧
